Articles.Content: Floor 971: My first code ever written is being operated. (It's a kOS rocket that I made this morning)
Floor 972: Measurements have detected a net energy outflow from this floor, but no one is able to find it despite ransacking every corner, nook and cranny. This floor is a huge mess.
Floor 973. WARNING! DO NOT PRESS BIG RED TEXT ACTIVATOR BUTTON!
Floor 974: You put on scuba gear, pass through an airlock, and find yourself at the bottom of a kilometer-tall cube of clear water, illuminated throughout by what appears to be Cherenkov radiation.
Floor 975. Jeb was here.
Floor 976: You see a horse. You tell him, "Why the long face?". The horse, unable to speak, takes a dump on the floor and walks away.

Floor 977 docm77 is seen playing ksp

(Youtube reference)
Floor 978. Congratulations, you are now IN SPAAAAAACE!

Floor 979: This floor contains nothing but computer labs full of 5-year-old Dells and 12-year-old kids playing Minecraft while screeching middle school profanities at each other.

Floor 979 may also contain The Loop, but this is unconfirmed.
980: this floor is overrun with teletubbies. you try to escape.

981. YOU FAILED! (go back to floor 1)

1. You find a spaceship (?) that elevates you back to floor 982.
you meet a button. you do not press it
983. There is another button. You do not press it.
984: you are hit by a train
985. Megatiger78 is killed by a teletubbie

This isn't Survive That Attack.

Floor 956: Light does not appear to work on this floor, as everything beyond the stairwell door is pitch black; you feel your way across it and into the stairwell to the next floor.
957: this game becomes survive that floor.

No way.

Floor 957: Vigilante justice appears to be established here. Masked men with guns wave you past and tell you that they're letting you go this time, but if they see you in here again, you're dead.
Floor 958: Minecraft- A Creeper explodes and sends you flying through and ceiling and to the next floor.
Floor 959: You suddenly find yourself quantum tunneling to the next floor!
Floor 960. This floor seems familar, and in one thousand and one floors the Soviets might do something amazing.
Floor 961: You hear some ominous giggling. You look out to see a few girls calling your name and calling you "cute". You, shocked, go to the next floor.
Floor 962: Shoe shopping. If you do that you lose a man card.
963: Matthew Santoro making said man card video.
